A3047 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-FBO-AVENGRS-LADN-(SLA     05-02 0524
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBO-AVENGRS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AVENGERS REMAIN WINLESS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ There's a school of thought that expansion teams
can immediately be competitive in the Arena Football League. So
far, the Los Angeles Avengers are doing nothing to bolster that
opinion.
</P>
<P>
   They remained winless Monday night after losing to the Oklahoma
Wranglers 59-33 before 9,160 at Staples Center.
</P>
<P>
   But they're not quite ready to admit it's impossible to become a
team capable of being in playoff contention.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not far off,'' quarterback Scott Semptimphelter said.
``We're just struggling. It's a very long season. We need to find a
niche and come together.''
</P>
<P>
   That makes L.A. 0-3 to open the season, and loss No. 4 appears
just a few days away when the Avengers play Friday at Oklahoma.
</P>
<P>
   It wasn't exactly the showing Avengers coach Stan Brock wanted,
especially since he coached the Wranglers last season, when they
were in Portland.
</P>
<P>
   Brock took a longer-than-usual amount of time in the locker room
after the game to give the Avengers his take on the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a lot of things going on in the players' minds,''
Brock said. ``They have to go back to work. It's just a matter of
getting everyone to play together.
</P>
<P>
   ``We played against a very good football team with some guys
that haven't seen any arena football. I'm not making excuses. We'll
learn from it.''
</P>
<P>
   The Avengers cured the turnover problem from their previous
game, but their kicking woes continued, as Kyle Pooler missed three
field goals. He also failed to convert an extra point because of a
bad snap.
</P>
<P>
   Wranglers quarterback Ron Lopez, who played for Pierce and
Glendale colleges before attending Utah State, completed 21 of 33
passes for 258 yards and six touchdowns. Semptimphelter completed
17 of 37 passes for 210 yards, three touchdowns and two
interceptions.
</P>
<P>
   Oklahoma (3-0) broke the game open in the third quarter, taking
a 42-19 lead on an 18-yard pass from Lopez to Barry Dillard. The
Avengers finally added a touchdown with 2:40 left as Semptimphelter
found Chris Jackson on a 34-yard touchdown to cut the deficit to
42-26, but L.A. never got closer.
</P>
<P>
   The first half was fairly close until the Wranglers made a late
run in the final five minutes.
</P>
<P>
   The Avengers trailed by five points (21-16) when Semptimphelter
flipped a 1-yard pass to Larry Thompson. But Oklahoma immediately
responded as Lopez hit Bobby McGowens on a 7-yard pass to give the
Wranglers a 28-16 lead.
</P>
<P>
   The Wranglers added a touchdown with three seconds left as Lopez
connected on a 17-yard pass to Melvin Phillips and a 35-16 lead.
Pooler hit a 47-yard field goal at the buzzer to cut Oklahoma's
halftime lead to 35-19.
</P>
<P>
   __ Notes: Quarterback Todd Marinovich, charged last week for
felony sexual assault, was not part of the active roster for the
game. Marinovich had been the backup quarterback fOcjQhe Avengers'
first three game. Quarterback Harry Leons was activated for the
first time this season. Marinovich attended the game in street
clothes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-02-00 0200EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
