<DOCNO> NYT20000502.0055 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-02 12:20 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3209 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-WRESTLING-BACKLASH-CO     05-02 0472
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-BACKLASH-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Return of the `Rattlesnake' highlight of WWF's `Backlash'
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   It has been a very strange month for the World Wrestling
Federation. It started with ````Wrestlemania'''' and concluded with
Sunday's ``Backlash'' pay-per-view, and in both cases, the draw was
not the wrestlers in the ring that day, but wrestlers of the past.
</P>
<P>
   For ``Wrestlemania'' it was seven hours of all the past
``Wrestlemania'' that helped boost buy rates to the highest of the
year. On Sunday, the WWF was banking on the draw of former champion
'Stone Cold' Steve Austin to help put over a pay-per-view that had
a repeat performance in the main event (The Rock vs. Triple H).
</P>
<P>
   Whether or not Austin helped the buy rates won't be known until
next week, but his dramatic return was the highlight of an average
pay-per-view.
</P>
<P>
   The first match of the night was a tag team championship bout
between Degeneration X's Road Dogg and X-Pac vs. the champions,
Edge and Christian. The match included the return of Debra. The
former valet who has been out of action while attending to her man,
Austin, while he recovers from neck surgery. She was the guest ring
announcer, but her return made it certain to fans that Austin would
be in the main event later in the night. The match was nothing
special and in what became a theme for the night, the champions
left with their titles. But during the match X-Pac injured his own
valet, Tori. This could be the beginning of the end for Tori and
DX. She may return to women's competition.
</P>
<P>
   The lightweight title was on the line as Scotty Too Hotty and
champion Dean Malenko end their `three matches in three weeks.'
Malenko left with the tile and Scotty will probably go back to tag
team matches with Grandmaster Sexy now that the Grandmaster has
recovered from knee surgery. The funniest match of the night was
Kurt Angle taking on the Big Show. Big Show continued to run down a
list of different gimmicks as he came to the ring dressed like Hulk
Hogan and proclaiming himself the `Showster.' Big Show hit most of
the Hulkster's moves, including his comebacks and had the crowd
chanting 'Hogan, Hogan'. The Show got the win.
</P>
<P>
   That led to the long-running feud between The Rock and Triple H.
As expected, the McMahons (Vince and Shane) did everything to keep
the Rock from winning, but when it seemed like all was lost, Austin
turned the tide for The Rock, using a chair to dispatch of trouble.
Linda McMahon made her way to the ring with fired WWF referee Earl
Hebner in tow. The Rock pinned Triple H to become the new WWF
champion. After a stare down, Austin joined The Rock in the ring
for a celebration, but don't expect a long friendship.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
