<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-LABELLA (Washington) _ Former federal prosecutor Charles
LaBella, who headed a Justice Department task force to investigate
possible campaign finance violations, outlines why he urged the
appointed of an independent counsel to investigate President
Clinton and Vice President Gore. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   MISSILE-DEFENSE (Washington) _ Three senior members of the
Russian Duma legislature warn U.S. lawmakers that if the White
House follows through on plans to build a national missile defense
system, the U.S.-Russia relationship will be severely destabilized.
One Duma member, Alexander Shabanov, said the missile defense
program could spark ``another Cold War,'' and he warned of ``very
dangerous'' repercussions. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-PRIMARIES (Washington) _ In an effort to halt the money and
media race among presidential candidates, a Republican Party
commission headed by former Sen. Bill Brock is recommending an
overhaul of primary elections. Under the plan, smaller states would
vote first in primaries staggered from March 1 to June 1. The plan
would put larger states such as California and New York back in the
line _ precisely where they had been prior to the 2000 season. By
DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   BANKRUPTCY-REFORM (Washington) _ Four liberal Democratic
congressmen joined labor and consumer advocates Tuesday to denounce
a bankruptcy reform bill they say punishes working Americans hit by
catastrophic illness. Sens. Paul Wellstone, D-Minn., Edward
Kennedy, D-Mass., and Russell Feingold , D-Wis., and Rep. Jerrold
Nadler, D-N.Y. said the bill would make it more difficult for
borrowers in financial trouble to avoid paying off their debts by
declaring bankruptcy. By AUSTIN ZALKIN.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CAMPBELL-SENATE (Washington) _ Foreign policy isn't a best
seller these days in American politics but Rep. Tom Campbell,
R-Calif., intends to put it stage center in his uphill race against
Sen. Dianne Feinstein, D-Calif. Campbell accuses her of abdicating
her role as a senator by tacitly endorsing last year's air war over
Yugoslavia, a conflict he says the U.S. had no business intervening
in. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
