secure the range's perimeter once protesters are removed. The
majority of protesters have said that they will not physically
resist the federal agents, but will have to be arrested to leave
the bombing range. Navy exercises that had been held for 60 years
on the island, just east of Puerto Rico, were suspended a year ago
after stray bombs killed a civilian security guard, releasing
pent-up resentment in the U.S. territory. Developing. (MWilliams,
Cox News Service). 15.
