<HEADER>
A3420 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX     05-02 0429
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
YOUNG SINGER STRIKES CHORD FOR FORD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Who is the teen-age girl who sings on Ford commercials? I
think she's from Scotland.
</P>
<P>
   _ D.W., Warwick, R.I.
</P>
<P>
   A: Welsh soprano Charlotte Church sings on the Ford ``Global
Anthem'' commercials.
</P>
<P>
   The 14-year-old singer recorded ``Just Wave Hello'' specifically
for the commercial, and it is included on her 1999 album,
``Charlotte Church.''
</P>
<P>
   After singing ``Pie Jesu'' on a television show at age 11,
Church was signed by Sony Music UK. Her debut album, ``Voice of an
Angel,'' sold more than 600,000 copies in the United Kingdom and
was a top-30 album in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   Church has an official fan club at Box 153, Stanmore, Middlesex
HA7 2HF, England, and a Web site at www.charlottechurch.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Who plays Judge Zoey Hiller on ABC's ``The Practice''?
</P>
<P>
   _ P.B., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: The judge is played by Linda Hunt, 55, who received a Viewers
for Quality Television award nomination in 1998 for the role.
</P>
<P>
   Hunt is best known for winning a Best Supporting Actress Oscar
playing Billy Kwan, a male character in 1982's ``The Year of Living
Dangerously.'' She's the only performer to win an Academy Award by
playing a character of the opposite sex.
</P>
<P>
   The actress, who grew up in Westport, Conn., works most often as
a narrator or voice artist. She portrays Grandmother Willow in the
Disney films ``Pocahantas'' and ``Pocahantas II'' and narrated the
documentary ``Paul Monette: The Brink of Summer's End'' in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Write to Hunt in care of William Morris Agency, 151 El Camino
Drive, Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Charlton Heston?
</P>
<P>
   _ N.P.H., Bedford, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Send your letter to him in care of International Creative
Management, 8942 Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills, CA 90211.
</P>
<P>
   Heston, 75, was elected president of the National Rifle
Association in 1998 and speaks frequently about gun-related issues.
</P>
<P>
   Though he continues to act, appearing in the movies ``Any Given
Sunday'' and ``Gideon'' in 1999, Heston makes news most often
because of his NRA affiliation. ``That's what happens when you
exchange a set of stone tablets for a shotgun,'' he told an
audience in March.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
