(Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Also moving in Entertainment (e) category
</P>
<P>
   ROBERDS-MAIN _ DAYTON _ Roberds Inc., the Ohio-based furniture,
appliance and electronics retailer, said Tuesday it has ceased
operations and closed all stores and distribution centers in Ohio
and Georgia. ``The inability to reach credit terms with our major
vendors resulted in our inability to provide merchandise for our
customers,'' said CEO Melvin Baskin. The move puts 1,300 employees
in Ohio and Georgia out of work and puts a serious dent in local
newspaper and television advertising budgets and tax receipts.
(Tresslar, Dayton Daily News). 30. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Dayton expects to move the stories in this package between
6 and 7 p.m. EDT.
</P>
