   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ Parents or grandparents could pour some cash into a
short-term savings plan for their high school or college graduates,
with goals such as paying college tuition or, later on, paying off
college loans. Family members might also lean towards buying stocks
or shares in a stock mutual fund, perhaps in a Roth IRA. With those
longer-term arrangements, the goal is to encourage young people to
start soon on their investment plans, so they can benefit from the
power of compounding. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
