enough reasons to second guess his senate race, the conservative
party has decided to proceed without him, nominating an
anti-abortion conservative who can be expected to paste Giuliani as
much as Hillary Clinton. By Fred Kaplan. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-ANTIBIOTICS (Boston) _ Massachusetts health officials are
trying to take a hard line with doctors who they say routinely
overprescribe antibiotics, contributing to the global problem of
drug resistance. By Richard Saltus. 800 words.
</P>
