   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ATT-REVAMP (Undated) _ AT&AMP;T's stock plunges as the company
issues its first profit warning under chief executive C. Michael
Armstrong, fueling worries about whether his radical remake of the
nation's largest long-distance company will succeed. By Peter Howe.
900 words.
</P>
<P>
   BIOGEN-MULLEN (Undated) _ James C. Mullen, named president of
Biogen after James Tobin left over apparent disagreements with
chairman Jim Vincent, will now become chief executive officer of
the biotechnology company. By Ronald Rosenberg. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   MEN-FAMILIES (Undated) _ While most polls have portrayed
American men as more concerned about power, prestige and money than
their families, new findings by the Radcliffe Public Policy Center
indicate younger men are more likely to put family matters first.
By Diane E. Lewis. 700 words.
</P>
