a Navy range on Vieques, a small island off Puerto Rico, even as
FBI officials continued to express misgivings about the operation
they will lead. Senior Pentagon officials have insisted that
protestors be removed from a bombing range on the island in before
training exercises begin. Louis J. Freeh, the FBI director, and
other senior law enforcement officials have warned of injuries, and
even casualties, as federal agents try to remove protesters from a
range scattered with live ammunition. By Elizabeth Becker.
