and counties, the nation's gun companies have broken off settlement
negotiations and are counting on sympathetic judges or a victory by
George W. Bush in November to help them before they are overwhelmed
by huge legal bills or potentially incriminating documents that may
be unearthed in the litigation. By Fox Butterfield.
</P>
