<HEADLINE>
JOBE WILL KEEP PHONE ON WITH FIRST CHILD DUE SOON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JIMMY BURCH 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ The mobile phone is charged and ready. It
ranks as the most indispensable item in Brandt Jobe's golf bag as
the Southlake resident makes final preparations for the GTE Byron
Nelson Classic and MasterCard Colonial.
</P>
<P>
   Jobe, 34, plans to play practice rounds at the host sites of
both local PGA Tour events this week. But he would prefer to be
called off the course by a call from his wife, Jennifer, who is due
May 14 with the couple's first child.
</P>
<P>
   ``The ideal situation would be to get the call Friday or
Saturday,'' said Jobe, who practices regularly at the Four Seasons
Resort in Irving, site of the Nelson tournament. ``That way, we'll
have family in town ... and Nelson week can be one, big
celebration. I think it would be pretty cool every year to be able
to celebrate your daughter's birthday in the same week as the Byron
Nelson.''
</P>
<P>
   Yes, he said ``daughter.'' The Jobes already know they're having
a girl, which has complicated the name game.
</P>
<P>
   ``People told us if it was a boy, we should name him Byron. But
what do you do with a girl ... call her Byretta? That doesn't sound
so good,'' said Jobe, who proudly peeled off his golf glove to
display a scar on his left index finger.
</P>
<P>
   ``Crib work,'' Jobe said. ``This is going to be a thrill. I just
hope little baby Jobe cooperates and I don't have to withdraw from
one of these events. If I do, I think everyone would understand.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
