r s BC-RAC-DERBY-NOTES-TEX     05-02 0339
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-DERBY-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TIM PRICE 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. _ The time looked good. But trainer Steve
Asmussen decided not to enter Snuck In for the Kentucky Derby
because the colt's work at five-eighths of a mile in 59 seconds _
the fastest of 26 horses at that distance yesterday at Churchill
Downs _ wasn't what Asmussen was hoping to see.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was looking for him to settle,'' Asmussen said. ``His
demeanor right now isn't one that would be successful on Derby
Day.''
</P>
<P>
   That demeanor showed when Snuck In, under exercise rider Krissie
Knorr, aggressively tossed his head as he and his work mate began
picking up speed toward the five-eighths pole. Snuck In was even
more of a handful before he made it in front of the clocker's stand
on the backstretch.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was real bad at the seven-eighths pole,'' Asmussen said.
</P>
<P>
   Asmussen said Snuck In is being pointed to the Preakness Stakes
on May 20.
</P>
<P>
   Asmussen also worked Lone Star Derby third-place finisher Big
Numbers yesterday. Big Numbers covered five-eighths of a mile in
1:001/5, fourth-fastest of the day at Churchill, and he's being
pointed to the May 13 Illinois Derby.  &QL; 
Other workouts
</P>
<P>
   Two other notable horses worked five-eighths yesterday: Captain
Steve went in 592/5 seconds, and The Deputy covered it in 1 minute.
Both Bob Baffert (trainer of Captain Steve) and Jenine Sahadi
(trainer of The Deputy) were pleased.
</P>
<P>
   Baffert said Captain Steve worked without blinkers after racing
with them the past seven starts and will go in the Derby with
blinkers off.  &QL; 
A spot for China
</P>
<P>
   Trainer Laura Wohlers said Ifitstobeitsuptome won't race in the
Derby, leaving the door open for China Visit to get into the field.
</P>
<P>
   China Visit is undefeated in two starts, including the United
Arab Emirates Derby, and was flown to Kentucky from Dubai last week
by Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid al Maktoum.
</P>
<P>
   China Visit galloped 11/2 miles yesterday and is scheduled to
work five-eighths today.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
