 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-DISNEY-TIMEWARNER-NYT (moved on Monday, May 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 1,
about the decision by Time Warner Cable to remove ABC stations from
cable systems in seven cities misstated the basis of ABC's move for
redress from the Federal Communications Commission. It was a 1993
commission regulation, not a clause in the 1992 Cable Act.
</P>
