a presidential primary schedule Tuesday that would let small states
vote first in early March, with clusters of larger states voting
later through June. ``We're concerned that too few people have a
say in the process,'' said Jim Nicholson, chairman of the
Republican National Committee. (Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
